bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I'm a 22-year-old nanny who recently moved to Atlanta from Kansas City. With 3 years of full-time nanny experience and a background as a PreK teacher, I've worked with children from infants to middle schoolers. Starting online school this summer, I'm seeking a part-time nanny position beginning in June. I'm creative, organized, and fun, and I love helping kids learn and grow. I'm happy to assist with household tasks and have a passion for dance and baking!

description.originalText: Ashlyn is super kind and communicative. She watched our toddler with confidence and was caring of our pets as well. We felt great with her at our house while we enjoyed a date at the soccer game! We would definitely book her again!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, my name is Emma ! I am currently a part time nanny to three girls (4, 5, and 7), and a certified Infant Care Specialist.

I am in the process of becoming a Newborn Care Specialist, and looking to gain more hours of experience with babies under 16 weeks.

I have experience with all ages (newborns to teenagers), and have over 12 years of experience, and over 3 years of professional nanny experience.
I have done volunteer work with my local church in their nursery and toddler classes, as well as taught cheerleading camp to 3-year-olds at my high school all four years.

CPR certified
Certified Infant Care Specialist
Animal lover (comfortable with any pets)
Fully vaccinated
First Aid certified
Completed Red Cross Water Safety class
Have own transportation
Non-smoker

description.displayText: We used Emma as an day time babysitter last week.  My wife, daughter, and I all liked her, she did a good job for what we asked of her.  We would use her again.

bio.experienceSummary: Having worked with kids of different ages for five years, I am a skilled and compassionate childcare provider. My enthusiasm for childcare is a result of my satisfying experiences in past babysitting positions and my wish to help families by offering a dependable daycare alternative. My approach is typically laid back and I allow children to be creative and think for themselves. I primarily worked with children who are raised in the Montessori style of parenting and I carry some of the lessons and allow your child the freedom to feel their emotions. I typically am not a fan of screen time but at the end of the day, I follow your style of parenting! Im flexible and always understanding

description.originalText: Kaira was wonderful! My oldest warmed up to her so quickly and asked for her the next day. She was great and so patient with the kids. She also helped out so much with cleaning bottles and dishes while they napped. Ended up being a lifesaver while I worked. We’ve had her over twice now, and we would recommend her to anyone needing help with their kids. Thank you, Kaira!

bio.experienceSummary: With a genuine love for children and years of experience, I provide a safe, nurturing environment where your little ones can thrive. From engaging activities to bedtime routines, rest assured your child is in capable hands. With a keen eye for safety and a playful spirit, I strive to make every moment enjoyable and memorable for your family. Let me be your trusted partner in childcare - because your child's happiness and well-being are my top priorities.

description.originalText: Monique is awesome! She has cared for our kids 2x and they love her. She is very attentive and the kids enjoy spending time with her. She is prepared and asked questions before each visit. She  follows our lead with kids care. We would love to continue working with her.

bio.experienceSummary: I have years experience(10+) in childcare. Over my career this has included occasional babysitting as well as regular, part time nanny positions. Caring and enthusiastic childcare provider with multiple years of experience in care taking and education. Patient, adaptable and comfortable supervising groups of children large and small. Hoping to better take advantage of my skill set in a nurturing, hands-on role.

Hello! 
 
I hope all is well! 

I am a compassionate and dedicated , committed to providing a nurturing and safe environment for children. I have a strong background in early childhood development, creating engaging educational activities, and managing daily routines. 

My skills include organizing age-appropriate activities, and supporting both children and families in achieving their goals. I hold certifications in First Aid and CPR. I am also fully vaccinated. I am adept at handling a variety of situations with patience and care. 

My goal is to foster a positive, supportive environment where children can thrive and grow! 

Help me, help you! 
I look forward to hearing from you!

description.originalText: Reyann is an amazing sitter!  My daughter loved her, and Reyann went out of her way to understand our needs in advance and accommodate our requests.  Most importantly my daughter loved her and can’t wait to see her again.  We will use her again without hesitation!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Shantell. I love kids. I love to read, draw, sing, dance, and design clothes. I have a great history of working with children, from infant to toddler. I have worked in a day care setting in Atlanta, GA and loved it. I gained so much experience and built a strong passion for child care. I have worked with children in a summer camp, taking field trips and designing arts and craft while staying out of the sun. I have also worked with seniors, I help take care of my great grandmother who had suffered from Alzheimer's. I have lots of reference available upon request. I have experience with date night, on call, live in companion, etc. I love children and child care is my passion. I will promise to provide a safe and comfortable environment to meet any of your needs! Experience working fulltime with a contract , live in overnight , ongoing care , reference available.
NCS- New born care certification 
CDA-child development associates/infant / toddler 
CNA-certified nurse asst

description.originalText: Shantell took care of my 2 kids (ages 1 and 3 at the time) and they very quickly warmed up to her.  She is friendly, flexible, creative and has a lot of patience :)  I recommend!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, 
I love caring and interacting with children. I'm a mother of a 12-year-old. I've nannied for five years with family. Nine years professional babysitter/nanny/house manager. I have experience in ECE three plus years. I also have nine plus years in housekeeping. I'm looking for a Full/Part-time positions. I have several references. On a lighter side, I'm great with pets, crafts and outdoor activities. I'm looking forward to meeting you and your families.

description.originalText: Shoshannia is the best nanny! She’s been taking care of our ten month old for seven months now (since I returned to work.) She puts his health and safety first, but they also have a ton of fun together. As a first time mom, I get nervous with every new milestone he’s going through (eating, walking, etc.), but Shoshannia’s experience and calming spirit always puts my mind at ease. My baby is very active, so I was worried about finding a nanny who could help him sleep, but he sleeps even better with Shoshannia who encourages him to stick to routines. She goes beyond taking care of him to taking care of our family: helping clean dishes, clean our baby’s room and kitchen, bringing goodies to share, offering warm hugs, and so much more. We also appreciate how she speaks Spanish to our baby and is kind to our cats (who have felt out of place since the baby arrived.) Our boy lights up when she arrives; he kicks his legs and crawls right over to give her a big hug. I would highly recommend Shoshannia as a nanny if you need one!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi I'm a very experienced childcare worker. I have experience working at a daycare. I'm a friendly Enthusiastic person, who truly cares about my job. I am responsible hard-working and also reliable. I look forward to meeting your family

description.displayText: Kalice is a very oriented person, she was well involved in the upbringing of my daughter. Kalice is dependable and very understanding, she had a great connection with my kid which I'm thankful for! Kalice is definitely one of the best

bio.experienceSummary: I have been in child care for over 25 years. I am a full time nanny but am looking for extra hours on evenings and weekends. I've worked with children of all ages in various jobs. I worked over 8 years for a residential treatment facility for troubled teens and have experience as a teacher assistant as well. I am a credentialed member of the International Nanny Association, have had training as a Newborn Specialist, am familiar with Moms On Call and am CPR and First Aid certified. I have several excellent references that I'm happy to share.

description.displayText: We've had Teri watch our toddler twice now and it's been great. This is our first time with a babysitter as our toddler was born right at the start of COVID so we've all been hunkered down together. Teri clearly enjoys caring for children, even if that just means accompanying our toddler as runs all around our backyard on repeat :) Thanks Teri, we can't wait to get you back out here again!
